news.title: SBI signs co-lending agreement with IIFL Home Finance for priority sector home loans
news.para: This is SBI's first co-lending agreement with a home finance company. The loan sourcing and servicing will be managed by IIFL HFL. Under the arrangement, 80% of the loan will be provided by SBI, according to the release.

news.title: Ahmedabad civic body, sub-registrar office to integrate property database
news.para: This is being done to arrest bogus documentation and ensure uniformity of records of property owners and tenants, claimed municipal officials.

news.title: Vadodara civic body to redevelop dilapidated houses for poor
news.para: VMC had constructed housing blocks for the economic weaker sections of the society under various schemes in the Tandalja, Tarsali, Navi Dharti, Bavchawad, Jetalpur Road and other areas over the years.

news.title: MahaRERA consumer group seeks transparent case disposals
news.para: Ahead of the CAC meeting on April 12, its consumer group members have sought timely execution of orders issued by the authorities. They are of the view that most orders issued are not executed. They also want live streaming of the meeting.

news.title: Development work under land pooling to be kick-started soon in Delhi
news.para: Earlier this month, the central government had proposed amendments to the Delhi Development Act, 1957, to make it obligatory for landowners to pool their properties once the owners of at least 70% of the developable area in an identified land-pooling sector had registered their holdings for pooling.

news.title: Colliers appoints Kanchana Krishnan as managing director-Chennai
news.para: With close to two decades of experience, Krishnan has held senior leadership roles at Knight Frank, Cushman & Wakefield, and most recently at JLL India.

news.title: Housing ministry approves construction of 2.02 lakh PMAY-Urban homes in eight states
news.para: The states where these homes will be constructed are Assam, Bihar, Jharkhand, Kerala, Madhya Pradesh, Odisha, Rajasthan and Tamil Nadu.

news.title: Goa RERA fines Mapusa builder for delay in project
news.para: In all, 36 unit holders had approached Goa RERA in 2019 after the builder failed to complete the building and hand over timely possession of the units to them.

news.title: Stanza Living closes Rs 425 crore debt financing from Kotak Mahindra, RBL & Alteria Capital
news.para: The money will be utilised to fund capital expenditure for Stanza Living’s current and future projects and accelerate the company's next phase of multi-city expansion. This debt infusion comes on the back of the solid $100 million equity funding raised by Stanza Living mid last year.

news.title: Two builders, three workers fined for noise pollution rules violation in Mumbai
news.para: Mumbai police chief Sanjay Pandey recently held meetings with developers where he had made it clear that construction activity would have to be limited to prescribed timings of 6am-10pm and decibel levels should not be higher than 65dB in residential areas.

news.title: Court rejects discharge plea of valuer in DHFL case
news.para: Refusing the plea of Sunil Chaudhary, the special court said, “No grounds exist to discharge the accused. On the contrary, the prima facie evidence and the circumstances are on record to proceed with the accused.”

news.title: Coworking firm iSprout raises $4 million in funding
news.para: In the funding round a substantial part has been invested by the director of one of India’s leading infrastructure companies. Post this round, over 75% ownership of the company is with the four co-founders and the invested infrastructure company’s director.

news.title: Gurugram: Flouted DTCP order, FIR filed against directors of Sai Aaina Farms
news.para: In March 2020, the district town planner (DTP) restrained the builder from further construction or development work at the site and sale and transfer of property after objections by another real estate company.

news.title: Gurugram: DTCP issues notices to 17 condominiums for giving possession without OCs
news.para: ​​In several towers of these projects developed by prominent realty companies like Unitech, Ansal, Vatika and Vipul, among others, families have been living for years without the mandatory document in violation of the Haryana Development and Regulation of Urban Areas Act, 1975, according to the town planner.

news.title: Illicit affair, fund diversion, the Max Group family feud veers towards a messy unraveling
news.para: In a petition filed before the NCLT, Neelu Analjit Singh also sought an investigation into the affairs of Max Ventures Investment Holdings Pvt Ltd and directions to declare Analjit Singh "unfit" to be a director and shareholder of the company.
